Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 367
Description.abstract: 20. ff. 183-186, [Hours of the Dead, Matins to Compline] Ad singulas horas de passione Christi pro defunctis. Ad matutinam...Et libera eam ob omni tribulacione et angustia sua. Amen.

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 373
Description.abstract: 21. ff. 186-188v. [Indulgence prayers] Hec oratio est XXXa diebus pro animabus dicenda...Metuende et tremende deus...ab omnibus penis et vinculis. Amen.

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 378
Description.abstract: 22. ff. 188v-192, [Glossed Paternoster] Pater noster qui es in celis indulge animabus qui te tam colendum et amandum...

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 385
Description.abstract: 23. ff. 192-194, [Glossed Ave Maria] Oratio devota ad dominam nostram pro animabus. Ave Maria ora pro anima famula tua...

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 389
Description.abstract: 24. ff. 194-201, [Marian prayers for the Dead] Oratio de domina nostra pro defunctis. O dulcissima virgo Maria obsecro te per gladium doloris ...sit nostra in te gloria per cuncta sempiterna secula. Amen.

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 403
Description.abstract: 25. ff. 201-205v, [Prayers for itemized episodes of the Passion interspersed with Pater nosters.] Incipiunt .XV. Paternoster pro animabus valde boni et utiles de singulis membris domini nostri Jhesu Christi. Pater noster. O dulcissime domine Jhesu Christe pro puncciones spinee corone...per tuam infenitam [sic] bonitatem et clemenciam. Amen.

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 412
Description.abstract: 26. ff. 205v-213v, [Additional Paternoster prayers for indulgences] Oratio valde utilis et devota triginta diebus pro animabus dicenda. Pater noster. Per amaritudines...sororis nostre suscipias in eodem amora spiritum eius.

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 429
Description.abstract: 27. ff. 214-216, Incipit obsequium beate Barbare .XV. diebus legendum in die sancti Clementis incipiendum usque ad festum concepcionis beate Marie virginis. O gloriosa sponsa Christi Barbara per illam qua sustinuisti...[With instructions: f. 214v, 3 Paternosters prostrate; 115, 3 Paternosters kneeling; 215v 3 Paternosters standing; 216 3 Paternosters kneeling with bowed head.]

Title: Coll. 170. Ms. 675. Page 434
Description.abstract: 28. ff. 216v-217, [Added prayer] O sapientia que ex ore altissimi prodisti attingens a fine usque ad finem...
